Description:
Location, Quality & Big Block!
This spacious home was built to exacting standards as a builders own home. Located in central Drysdale on an 807m2 allotment with adjoining reserve this double storey residence offers family and meals areas downstairs overlooking delightfully landscaped gardens, a fully equipped timber kitchen complete with granite bench tops & double oven plus access to extensive outdoor living & entertainment area. Downstairs we also have bedrooms 2 & 3- both double in size with plenty of wardrobe space, the main bathroom, laundry with loads of storage & huge WI linen cupboard. The master bedroom is of generous proportions and is located upstairs and has a full ensuite & walk in wardrobe. The 2nd living zone is also upstairs and opens onto a timber balcony with views overlooking the reserve towards Geelong. Incorporated into this living area is a study nook perfect for the home office. The home is kept comfortable all year round by central gas heating & reverse cycle air conditioning. Larger than average double garage & workshop, ducted vacuum system, double glazed windows, instant gas HWS and extensive brick paving to name but a few features on offer. Properties of this caliber need to be viewed to appreciate.
Maree Humphrey : 0408 504 042

Description:
What a Winner!
You can write your own profit cheque on the potential in this property. With so many outstanding options, the income you could generate here is a serious concern so get your bidding arm warmed up because bargains like this are as rare as hens teeth!
The most important points to note with 2 Eversley are:
Location
Size
Subdivision and
Rental/Resale
Situated right opposite the Drysdale Shopping Centre, aged care and community health centre and within walking distance of Neighbourhood centre, kindergarten, schools and medical/health facilities, you simply could not find a more convenient location.
The 809sqm corner block is absolutely PERFECT for subdivision (STCA) and would provide two substantial homes for rental or resale.
The existing clad dwelling is in amazing condition being first constructed in the art deco 1950s. It comprises 2 very generous bedrooms, a large lounge and separate dining leading onto the spacious central kitchen. An updated bathroom and partially renovated laundry room and rear entry/mudroom are ideal for first home buyers or retirees and the possibility to continue the modernisation whilst incorporating beautiful period features such as hardwood strip timber floors, deco cornicing and light fittings would make for a stunning contemporary home.
Presented in a neat, tidy, well maintained manner, it does not require much imagination or vision to be able to see this property for what it is...a goldmine!
- 809 sqm approx.
- Walk to everything
- Directly opposite shopping centre
- Spacious rooms/original features
- Development potential
Land: 809 sq m approx.

Description:
Unique Development Opportunity
Being presented for sale for the first time in over 50 years this rare Drysdale piece of land offers a once in a life time opportunity for the lucky buyer. The opportunity to secure 2590m2 approx or prime land in the heart of Drysdale will provide the lucky purchaser with endless opportunities.
Subdivide and develop a multi townhouse cul-de-sac (STCA) or build your dream home. This property is highly suited to builders and investors alike looking to capitalize in this wonderful part of town. Located within close walking distance to local schools, shops and sporting facilties makes this property ideal for the growing family looking to add value whilst retaining a huge back yard with plenty of space for the kids. The existing dwelling includes separate lounge and kitchen, bathroom, 3 large bedrooms all with original fittings aswell as an outside pool house.
Look no further in your quest to live right in the heart of Drysdale with this exceptional parcel of land. Make your appointment today as this property is sure to attract many buyers from all over the region.

Description:
When A Quality Lifestyle Matters
This exceptional broad acre property of 76acres - 30.76ha (approx.) zoned rural offers a magnificent family lifestyle in a sought after central area of the Bellarine Peninsula - just minutes from Drysdale Central, an assortment of schools, restaurants and beaches plus a private tennis court all adding to recreational options available here. The property features a private lake fed by a tree lined stream, fascinating birdlife, four dams, cattle crush/yards, hay shed and also lends itself to a range of agricultural pursuits.
Enhanced by a refurbished 30sq residence which features tiled entrance foyer, brilliant zoned family accommodation with tranquil garden vistas, light-filled north-facing formal and informal living areas and expansive deck for outdoor entertaining; study, six bedrooms (BIRs, main/ensuite), bathroom, powder room and large laundry plus well-equipped kitchen with walk-in pantry. Other features include new carpets, ample storage, slab heating, OFPs, R/C airconditioner, town water, 13,000ltr water tank with garden irrigation system, 3-car garage.

Description:
Light, Bright and Funky
As close to new as it gets without having to endure the process of building yourself, this funky, split level 4 bedroom home offers first home buyers and young families an opportunity to start out with an eye for style. Designed and constructed with clever planning and careful thought, it maximises the advantages of the 617sqm block and is flooded with natural light.
Featuring polished timber floors and stairs, open design and contemporary feel, you will enjoy the space and lifestyle offered. Wow your friends and spread right out on the lower level in the spacious open plan living area which consists of a kitchen just begging to entertain (with its 900mm stainless steel Lofra appliances, dishwasher space and masses of storage), meals area, opening to entertaining deck, and lounge with stunning gas log fire. This area provides both a view and access to the huge deck and spacious sunny garden at the rear of the home, ideal for bbqs and summer evenings with friends. An ideal place for the kids to play with loads of room for them to run, the yard is safe, secure and clearly visible from the home.
The bedrooms are spacious, with the master bedroom featuring a large walk in robe and ensuite with double shower, and the remaining three have ample built in storage and share the upper level with a family bathroom, separate wc and handy linen.
Add to the layout the architectural features, rendered exterior, designer lighting and plush carpets, data network cabling in every room PLUS the location within walking distance of shops, schools and the Bellarine Rail Trail and you have everything you could possibly ask for.
- 617 sqm approx.
- Walk to shops, schools
- 2 years young
- Striking architectural features
- Large double garage
Land: 617 sq m approx.
